name: Zucchini Baked Appetizers
author: Beverly McDonald
summary: This is a family favorite. I make these and freeze slices between waxed paper. Put into a freezer bag and winter blahs are lifted when eating summer veggies. This is a great little freezer-friendly appetizer for the holidays or any get-together.
directions: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray
Mix together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, and pepper in a shallow bowl
Place zucchini in a separate bowl and toss with olive oil until coated
Dip each slice of zucchini into the bread crumb mixture to evenly coat
Place on the prepared baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until zucchini is tender and bread crumbs are golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes
